QUALIFICATION: the validity of the name Lepismodes is uncertain. It appeared twice in 1863; first, in the handwritten proceedings of a meeting which were apparently lithographically copied and circulated but not widely so that it was overlooked by other Thysanura workers until used by Delany, M.J. 1953. A revision of the British Thysanura. Entomologist's Monthly Magazine 89: 144-145; and second, in a conventional print but with such an inadequte description that the name was considered a nom. nud.
